title: Kevin McCarthy says he won't run again for House speaker
description: Earlier on Tuesday, the California Republican was defiant and said he would fight efforts to strip him of the speaker's gavel. Those efforts were ultimately successful.

title: Trump ally Kari Lake jumps into the Arizona Senate race
description: Republican Kari Lake, a Trump ally who lost the race for Arizona governor last year to Democrat Katie Hobbs, announced that she plans to run for Senate in next year’s election.

title: Nonunion autoworkers are watching the UAW — and deciding whether they want in
description: It isn’t just UAW members who are watching the expanding strikes at GM, Ford and Stellantis plants. Nonunion autoworkers at rival companies are paying attention, too.

title: Weeks into the Covid booster rollout, parents of young children say the shots are scarce
description: Since the government cleared the latest round of Covid boosters, parents say it’s been hard to make appointments to get their young kids vaccinated against the virus.

title: First person of color to be president of WGA East talks crucial timing of position
description: Television writer Lisa Takeuchi Cullen is making history as the first person of color to lead WGA East, and she’s not thrilled about it.

title: Here's who might testify in Sam Bankman-Fried fraud trial: Parents, ex-girlfriend Ellison, Scaramucci
description: On day one of Sam Bankman-Fried’s criminal trial, assistant U.S. attorney, Danielle Sassoon, rattled off a lengthy list of potential witnesses who might be called to testify for either the government or the defense.

title: House votes to remove McCarthy as speaker
description: The House of Representatives has voted to remove Rep. Kevin McCarthy, R-Cali., as Speaker of the House. NBC News' Garrett Haake reports on how both parties voted and who is next in line to take over as speaker.

title: Lady Gaga doesn't have to pay $500,000 to woman charged in connection to stealing her dogs
description: Lady Gaga has prevailed in a legal battle connected to the 2021 theft of her two French bulldogs, Koji and Gustav.

title: Judge orders Trump to delete 'disparaging' post about his law clerk and threatens sanctions
description: The judge presiding over Donald Trump's $250 million civil fraud trial in New York issued a partial gag order in the case Tuesday after the former president trashed the judge's law clerk on social media.

title: Senior Defense Department official charged with helping run dogfights
description: A senior Defense Department official has been charged with helping run a dogfighting ring in Maryland in which dogs were allegedly electrocuted if they lost.

title: Sen. Laphonza Butler is sworn in, filling Dianne Feinstein's seat
description: Butler was the president of EMILY's List and is the third Black woman to ever serve in the U.S. Senate.

description: A 17-year-old Ohio girl died after collapsing on a football field during homecoming festivities at her high school on Friday, according to the Mapleton Local School District.

description: Miami Heat player Jimmy Butler’s new “emo” hairdo is the internet’s latest obsession.

title: Speaker Kevin McCarthy is on the ropes. Here are some possible successors.
description: Rep. Matt Gaetz's effort to oust House Speaker Kevin McCarthy is uncertain, but that hasn’t stopped speculation about who could succeed him in the top job.

title: What happens next if Kevin McCarthy is ousted as Speaker of the House
description: Here are the next steps if the House votes in favor of ousting Kevin McCarthy as speaker. It would be the first time the House has voted a speaker out of office.

title: It's October 3, and 'Mean Girls' is now on TikTok— in 23 parts
description: In honor of the October 3 “Mean Girls” holiday, Paramount Plus has released the full movie on TikTok. The film starring Lindsay Lohan first hit theaters in 2004.

title: 11-year-old arrested and charged in shooting of 2 teens at Florida football practice
description: An 11-year-old boy allegedly shot two 13-year-olds after they had scuffled at a youth football practice in central Florida on Monday night, authorities said.

description: The House will vote on a Rep. Matt Gaetz motion to try to oust Kevin McCarthy as speaker Tuesday as the Republican leader remains defiant.

title: Texas forces changes on Latino and Black parents as Legislature debates school choice
description: In Houston, Texas the forced overhaul of some district schools that are majority Latino and Black takes place amid a history of racism and racial inequity in schools.

title: Biden to call world leaders and try to reassure them on U.S. support for Ukraine
description: President Joe Biden plans to hold a call with world leaders Tuesday in an effort to reassure allies about U.S. support for Ukraine, according to three administration officials.

title: Fleetwood Mac singer Stevie Nicks gets her own Barbie — and it's already sold out
description: Music legend Stevie Nicks officially has her own Barbie doll — and it sold out in less than 24 hours.

title: A pro-Putin populist’s success adds to fears of cracks in support for Ukraine
description: Robert Fico's election victory in Slovakia was a boost for Vladimir Putin and a blow to Ukraine as cracks begin to show in the West's support after the U.S. budget deal.

title: More Latinas are living in states with abortion bans and restrictions
description: More Latinas, close to 6.7 million, are living in the 26 states that have banned or are likely to ban abortions, a new analysis from the National Partnership for Women & Families and the National Latina Institute for Reproductive Justice found.

title: Drugmakers agree to negotiate drug prices with government, White House says
description: Major drugmakers have agreed to participate in Medicare price negotiations under the Inflation Reduction Act. The Biden administration aims to lower the prices of costly drugs.

title: Family of girl abducted from N.Y. park expresses relief at her return as suspect is charged
description: The family of Charlotte Sena, the 9-year-old girl who authorities said was abducted from a New York state park Saturday before she was found alive hiding in the cupboard of a trailer two days later, shared a message of relief as her alleged abductor was arraigned on a kidnapping charge.

title: Former Detroit police chief James Craig enters the GOP Senate race in Michigan
description: Former Detroit police chief James Craig, a candidate for Michigan’s GOP primary for governor last year, says he will seek the state’s open Senate seat in 2024.

title: Shooting at luxury shopping mall in Bangkok kills 3; 14-year-old suspect is in police custody
description: Police in Thailand arrested a 14-year-old suspected gunman after a shooting on Tuesday at a luxury mall in the capital Bangkok that authorities said killed three people and injured four others.

title: Trump says he will testify in 'scam' New York attorney general civil fraud trial
description: Trump returns to court for second day of arguments in fraud trial

description: A case involving the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau is one of several conservative-backed efforts before the justices aimed at weakening federal agencies.

title: Hunter Biden to be arraigned in Delaware on gun charges
description: Hunter Biden is expected to plead not guilty to three firearms charges during his arraignment in a federal court in Delaware on Tuesday/

title: Former NFL player Russ Francis among 2 killed in Lake Placid plane crash
description: Former NFL tight end Russ Francis, a three-time Pro Bowl selection with the New England Patriots who won a Super Bowl with the 1984 San Francisco 49ers, was killed along with another aviation enthusiast when their small plane crashed after takeoff from an upstate New York airport, authorities said Monday.

title: 2 U.S. soldiers dead after military vehicle flips over in Alaska

title: Late-night TV shows return after monthslong writers strike

title: Body camera video released after man is injured in Florida arrest
description: Law enforcement body camera video was released Monday in the violent Friday arrest of a 24-year-old Black man who suffered what appeared to be significant facial swelling in the encounter.

title: Texas congressman is victim of carjacking in Washington, D.C.
description: Democratic Rep. Henry Cuellar was the victim of an armed carjacking about a mile from the Capitol on Monday night. His office said he was not injured.

title: Kansas police chief who approved raid on journalists resigns
description: The police chief of a small Kansas town who directed searches of a publisher and his newsroom over its retrieval of public information has resigned, a city official told The Associated Press.

title: Nightly News Full Broadcast (October 2nd)
description: Trump back in New York court for civil fraud trial; General Milley: China is a ‘very capable’ intelligence collection organization; Rep. Gaetz moves to oust McCarthy as House Speaker; and more on tonight’s broadcast.

title: Investigators in Biden impeachment inquiry to question federal prosecutor
description: Matthew Graves, the U.S. Attorney for Washington, D.C., will sit for a voluntary transcribed interview on Tuesday, sources confirmed to NBC News.

title: Trump ramps up violent rhetoric
description: Former President Donald Trump is lashing out at political and legal foes in increasingly violent terms as his campaign to return to office accelerates.
